<font color="#FF0000">RAIN IS PEACEFUL!</font><br>
<tt>Sat Dec  6 22:57:57 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
When I was a small boy, we had a tin roof on our house.  The sound of rain falling onto that tin would always put me to sleep.  The smell of plowed fields after a rain are impressed into my mind as is the smell of ozone following a downpour.<br>
One night, while on the Omega operation, it rained for the fist time in a long time.  We had stashed our gear in an old tin shack.  When the rain came, I took a journey back in time and was a boy again.  Although we were in a precarious position with no security and no comforts, I managed to sleep through the night.  It was the best R&amp;R a man could have had!  I was far away from the war and my poncho was better than any down filled comforter!<br><br>
MTF
